Cauliflower Soup

1 head cauliflower
evoo
1 medium yellow onion
sea salt and freshly ground pepper
3-4 c low sodium chicken broth or vegetable broth
2 slices gf bread cut in 1/2" dice
ancho chile powder 

Trim the leafy bottom from the cauliflower. Cut (including the core) into small florets and 1/2" pieces. Heat 3 tbsp oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add the onion, season with salt and cook, stirring ofen, until softened, ~6min. Add 3 c of broth and bring to a boil. Add the cauliflower, cover, and simmer until fork tender, 8-10 min. Puree the soup with an immersion blender, adding more broth as needed until smooth. Season with salt and pepper. Heat 2 tbsp oil in a non-stick skillet over medium heat for 2 min. Add the bread cubes and cook for 1 min; toss in the pan and sprinkle generously with chile powder. Cook until bread is hot and beginning to crisp. They will crisp more as they cool. 
Serve soup with croutons on top
